the-css.escape()-method.name: escape
the-css.escape()-method.summary: The CSS.escape() static method returns a CSSOMString containing the escaped string passed as parameter, mostly for use as part of a CSS selector.
the-css.escape()-method.title: CSS.escape()

the-css.escape()-method.name: CSS
the-css.escape()-method.summary: The CSS interface holds useful CSS-related methods. No object with this interface are implemented: it contains only static methods and therefore is a utilitarian interface.
the-css.escape()-method.title: CSS

cssgroupingrule.name: CSSGroupingRule
cssgroupingrule.summary: An object implementing the CSSGroupingRule interface represents any CSS at-rule that contains other rules nested within it.
cssgroupingrule.title: CSSGroupingRule

the-cssmediarule-interface.name: CSSMediaRule
the-cssmediarule-interface.summary: The CSSMediaRule interface represents a single CSS @media rule. It implements the CSSConditionRule interface, and therefore the CSSGroupingRule and the CSSRule interface with a type value of 4 (CSSRule.MEDIA_RULE).

firefox.notes: Before Firefox 20, conditionText could not be set.

firefox_android.notes: Before Firefox 20, conditionText could not be set.

the-cssmediarule-interface.title: CSSMediaRule

dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.name: namespaceURI
dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.summary: The CSSNamespaceRule.namespaceURI read-only property returns a DOMString containing the text of the URI of the given namespace.
dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.title: CSSNamespaceRule.namespaceURI

dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.name: prefix
dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.summary: The CSSNamespaceRule.prefix read-only property returns a DOMString with the name of the prefix associated to this namespace. If there is no such prefix, returns  null.
dom-cssnamespacerule-namespaceuri.title: CSSNamespaceRule.prefix

the-cssnamespacerule-interface.name: CSSNamespaceRule
the-cssnamespacerule-interface.summary: The CSSNamespaceRule interface describes an object representing a single CSS @namespace at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface, with a type value of 10 (CSSRule.NAMESPACE_RULE).
the-cssnamespacerule-interface.title: CSSNamespaceRule

the-csspagerule-interface.name: CSSPageRule
the-csspagerule-interface.summary: CSSPageRule is an interface representing a single CSS @page rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 6 (CSSRule.PAGE_RULE).
the-csspagerule-interface.title: CSSPageRule

dom-cssrule-csstext.name: cssText
dom-cssrule-csstext.summary: The cssText property of the CSSRule interface returns the actual text of a CSSStyleSheet style-rule.
dom-cssrule-csstext.title: CSSRule.cssText

dom-cssrule-parentstylesheet.name: parentStyleSheet
dom-cssrule-parentstylesheet.summary: The parentStyleSheet property of the CSSRule interface returns the StyleSheet object in which the current rule is defined.
dom-cssrule-parentstylesheet.title: CSSRule.parentStyleSheet

css-rules.name: CSSRule
css-rules.summary: The CSSRule interface represents a single CSS rule. There are several types of rules, listed in the Type constants section below.
css-rules.title: CSSRule

the-cssrulelist-interface.name: CSSRuleList
the-cssrulelist-interface.summary: A CSSRuleList is an (indirect-modify only) array-like object containing an ordered collection of CSSRule objects.
the-cssrulelist-interface.title: CSSRuleList

dom-cssstyledeclaration-csstext.name: cssText
dom-cssstyledeclaration-csstext.summary: The cssText property of the CSSStyleDeclaration interface returns or sets the text of the element's inline style declaration only.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-csstext.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.cssText

dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyprior.name: getPropertyPriority
dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyprior.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyPriority() method interface returns a DOMString that provides all explicitly set priorities on the CSS property.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyprior.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyPriority()

dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyvalue.name: getPropertyValue
dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyvalue.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyValue() method interface returns a DOMString containing the value of a specified CSS property.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-getpropertyvalue.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.getPropertyValue()

dom-cssstyledeclaration-item.name: item
dom-cssstyledeclaration-item.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.item() method interface returns a CSS property name from a CSSStyleDeclaration by index
dom-cssstyledeclaration-item.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.item()

dom-cssstyledeclaration-length.name: length
dom-cssstyledeclaration-length.summary: The read-only property returns an integer that represents the number of style declarations in this CSS declaration block.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-length.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.length

dom-cssstyledeclaration-parentrule.name: parentRule
dom-cssstyledeclaration-parentrule.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.parentRule read-only property returns a CSSRule that is the parent of this style block
dom-cssstyledeclaration-parentrule.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.parentRule

dom-cssstyledeclaration-removeproperty.name: removeProperty
dom-cssstyledeclaration-removeproperty.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.removeProperty() method interface removes a property from a CSS style declaration object.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-removeproperty.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.removeProperty()

dom-cssstyledeclaration-setproperty.name: setProperty
dom-cssstyledeclaration-setproperty.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration.setProperty() method interface sets a new value for a property on a CSS style declaration object.
dom-cssstyledeclaration-setproperty.title: CSSStyleDeclaration.setProperty()

the-cssstyledeclaration-interface.name: CSSStyleDeclaration
the-cssstyledeclaration-interface.summary: The CSSStyleDeclaration interface represents an object that is a CSS declaration block, and exposes style information and various style-related methods and properties.
the-cssstyledeclaration-interface.title: CSSStyleDeclaration

dom-cssstylerule-selectortext.name: selectorText
dom-cssstylerule-selectortext.summary: The CSSRule.selectorText property gets the textual representation of the selector for the rule set. This is readonly in some browsers; to set stylesheet rules dynamically cross-browser, see Using dynamic styling information.
dom-cssstylerule-selectortext.title: CSSStyleRule.selectorText

dom-cssstylerule-style.name: style
dom-cssstylerule-style.summary: The CSSRule.style property is the CSSStyleDeclaration interface for the declaration block of the CSSRule.
dom-cssstylerule-style.title: CSSStyleRule.style

the-cssstylerule-interface.name: CSSStyleRule
the-cssstylerule-interface.summary: CSSStyleRule represents a single CSS style rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 1 (CSSRule.STYLE_RULE).
the-cssstylerule-interface.title: CSSStyleRule

dom-cssstylesheet-cssrules.name: cssRules
dom-cssstylesheet-cssrules.summary: The read-only CSSStyleSheet property cssRules returns a live CSSRuleList which provides a real-time, up-to-date list of every CSS rule which comprises the stylesheet.
dom-cssstylesheet-cssrules.title: CSSStyleSheet.cssRules

dom-cssstylesheet-deleterule.name: deleteRule
dom-cssstylesheet-deleterule.summary: The CSSStyleSheet method deleteRule() removes a rule from the stylesheet object.
dom-cssstylesheet-deleterule.title: CSSStyleSheet.deleteRule()

dom-cssstylesheet-insertrule.name: insertRule
dom-cssstylesheet-insertrule.summary: The CSSStyleSheet.insertRule() method inserts a new CSS rule into the current style sheet, with some restrictions.
dom-cssstylesheet-insertrule.title: CSSStyleSheet.insertRule()

dom-cssstylesheet-ownerrule.name: ownerRule
dom-cssstylesheet-ownerrule.summary: The read-only CSSStyleSheet property ownerRule returns the CSSImportRule corresponding to the @import at-rule which imported the stylesheet into the document.
dom-cssstylesheet-ownerrule.title: CSSStyleSheet.ownerRule

cssstylesheet.name: CSSStyleSheet
cssstylesheet.summary: The CSSStyleSheet interface represents a single CSS stylesheet, and lets you inspect and modify the list of rules contained in the stylesheet.
cssstylesheet.title: CSSStyleSheet

dom-elementcssinlinestyle-style.name: style
dom-elementcssinlinestyle-style.summary: The style property is used to get as well as set the inline style of an element. When getting, it returns a CSSStyleDeclaration object that contains a list of all styles properties for that element with values assigned for the attributes that are defined in the element's inline style attribute.
dom-elementcssinlinestyle-style.title: ElementCSSInlineStyle.style

the-linkstyle-interface.name: LinkStyle
the-linkstyle-interface.summary: The LinkStyle interface provides access to the associated CSS style sheet of a node.
the-linkstyle-interface.title: LinkStyle

dom-medialist-mediatext.name: mediaText
dom-medialist-mediatext.summary: The mediaText property of the MediaList interface is a stringifier that returns a DOMString representing the MediaList as text, and also allows you to set a new MediaList.
dom-medialist-mediatext.title: MediaList.mediaText

the-medialist-interface.name: MediaList
the-medialist-interface.summary: The MediaList interface represents the media queries of a stylesheet, e.g. those set using a <link> element's media attribute.
the-medialist-interface.title: MediaList

dom-stylesheet-disabled.name: disabled
dom-stylesheet-disabled.summary: The disabled property of the StyleSheet interface determines whether the style sheet is prevented from applying to the document.
dom-stylesheet-disabled.title: StyleSheet.disabled

dom-stylesheet-href.name: href
dom-stylesheet-href.summary: The href property of the StyleSheet interface returns the location of the style sheet.
dom-stylesheet-href.title: Stylesheet.href

dom-stylesheet-media.name: media
dom-stylesheet-media.summary: The media property of the StyleSheet interface specifies the intended destination media for style information. It is a read-only, array-like MediaList object and can be removed with deleteMedium() and added with appendMedium().
dom-stylesheet-media.title: StyleSheet.media

dom-stylesheet-ownernode.name: ownerNode
dom-stylesheet-ownernode.summary: The ownerNode property of the StyleSheet interface returns the node that associates this style sheet with the document.
dom-stylesheet-ownernode.title: StyleSheet.ownerNode

dom-stylesheet-parentstylesheet.name: parentStyleSheet
dom-stylesheet-parentstylesheet.summary: The parentStyleSheet property of the StyleSheet interface returns the style sheet, if any, that is including the given style sheet.
dom-stylesheet-parentstylesheet.title: StyleSheet.parentStyleSheet

dom-stylesheet-title.name: title
dom-stylesheet-title.summary: The title property of the StyleSheet interface returns the advisory title of the current style sheet.
dom-stylesheet-title.title: StyleSheet.title

dom-stylesheet-type.name: type
dom-stylesheet-type.summary: The type property of the StyleSheet interface specifies the style sheet language for the given style sheet.
dom-stylesheet-type.title: StyleSheet.type

stylesheet.name: StyleSheet
stylesheet.summary: An object implementing the StyleSheet interface represents a single style sheet. CSS style sheets will further implement the more specialized CSSStyleSheet interface.
stylesheet.title: StyleSheet

the-stylesheetlist-interface.name: StyleSheetList
the-stylesheetlist-interface.summary: The StyleSheetList interface represents a list of StyleSheet.
the-stylesheetlist-interface.title: StyleSheetList

dom-window-getcomputedstyle.name: getComputedStyle
dom-window-getcomputedstyle.summary: The Window.getComputedStyle() method returns an object containing the values of all CSS properties of an element, after applying active stylesheets and resolving any basic computation those values may contain.

firefox.notes: Before version 62 this function returned null when called on a Window with no presentation (e.g. an iframe with display: none; set). Since 62 it returns a CSSStyleDeclaration object with length 0, containing empty strings (bug 1467722; also see bug 1471231 for further work).

firefox_android.notes: Before version 62 this function returned null when called on a Window with no presentation (e.g. an iframe with display: none; set). Since 62 it returns a CSSStyleDeclaration object with length 0, containing empty strings (bug 1467722; also see bug 1471231 for further work).

dom-window-getcomputedstyle.title: Window.getComputedStyle()

css-style-sheet-collections.name: alternate_stylesheet
css-style-sheet-collections.summary: Specifying alternative style sheets in a web page provides a way for users to see multiple versions of a page, based on their needs or preferences.
css-style-sheet-collections.title: Alternative style sheets
